# Styling Rules

These rules apply strongly to:

- PublicLayout
- AuthLayout
- DashboardLayout
- route wrappers
- headers
- footers
- sidebars
- stage containers

Shells should create clear box-model boundaries.

Prefer:

```tsx
min-h-screen flex flex-col
```

Header/footer/sidebar wrappers should usually use:

```tsx
w-full shrink-0
```

Main stage areas should usually use:

```tsx
flex-1 w-full min-w-0
```

Content constraints belong inside sections.

Prefer:

```tsx
<section className="w-full">
  <div className="mx-auto w-full max-w-* px-*">Content</div>
</section>
```

Prefer:

- mobile first
- readable Tailwind
- full-width shells
- constrained content areas
- explicit layouts

Avoid when possible:

- fixed widths
- large min widths
- desktop-first styling
- hidden overflow
- shell content mixed with page content

These rules are softer for:

- modals
- drawers
- seating canvas
- drag systems
- highly custom UI

Prioritize:

```txt
Predictable > clever

Readable > reusable

Simple > abstract
```
